---
title: One-Pan Orzo Marinara with Chicken Sausage and Crispy Breadcrumbs
description: If there’s a cooking equivalent of an “easy” button, it’s the one-pan recipe—there’s no random kitchen doodads to search for, no hours spent cleaning. So if easy is what you’re looking for, you’ve come to the right place. Even the orzo pasta here skips the usual separate pot of boiling water and cooks right in the tomato sauce, along with the sausage, onion, and kale. The final step, in which the whole thing is baked to give it a crispy, cheesy finish, doesn’t even need a casserole dish—as long as your pan is ovenproof, it can go straight in the oven.
